<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Best Cable Arm Workout Routine</h2>



<p>Are you ready to start with a cable arm workout routine but unsure where to start?&nbsp;</p>



<p>This is a perfect <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/beginner-arm-workout" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">beginner arm workout</a> but can also be used by experienced lifters. Just ensure that you adjust your weight to match your fitness level.</p>



<p>You can do this by first determining your <a href="https://sportsmedicine-open.springeropen.com/articles/10.1186/s40798-020-00260-z" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">one repetition maximum</a>. This is the maximum weight you can lift for one repetition with good form.</p>



<p>Then, use the following ranges to help you figure out how heavy to lift:</p>



<ul>
<li><strong>Strength Training — </strong>80%–100% of your 1RM.</li>



<li><strong>Hypertrophy Training</strong> <strong>—</strong> 60%–80% of your 1RM.</li>



<li><strong>Endurance Training</strong> <strong>—</strong> 40%–60% of your 1RM.</li>



<li><strong>Power Training—</strong> 80%–100% of your 1RM.</li>
</ul>



